The paper discusses the use of bibliometric measures in evaluating academic publications in specific fields, namely biomedicine and economics. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), computational complexity (cs.CY), information retrieval (cs.IR), and software engineering (cs.SD). However, given the focus on bibliometrics and evaluation of academic publications, cs.DL and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CY, cs.IR, and cs.SD.
